cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CV (Computer Vision): The paper proposes a novel visual context-aware filter generation module for convolutional neural networks (CNNs) that incorporates contextual information present in images. 
2. cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper proposes a new technique for generating input-conditioned convolution filters that can enhance the modeling capacity of CNNs. 
3. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper proposes a new approach for achieving transformation-invariant neural networks, which is an important problem in AI. 
4. cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing): The paper proposes a new technique for generating convolution filters that can be used to enhance the performance of neural networks. 
5. cs.MM (Multimedia): The paper makes use of visualization techniques to demonstrate the effectiveness of the proposed visual context-aware convolution filters.
